config HEARTBEAT_LED
    bool "RGB status indicator via onboard WS2812 NeoPixel"
    default n
    help
      Uses the Waveshare RP2040-Zero onboard WS2812 NeoPixel (GP16, aliased as
      'led-strip' in the board DTS) to show three distinct status colours:

        Blue  1 Hz blink  = board is powered and ZMK is running (heartbeat)
        Green 150 ms flash = key detected on THIS half (UART TX proxy)
        Red   150 ms flash = key received from the OTHER half (UART RX proxy)
                             Central (left) only: position col >= 6

      Requires CONFIG_LED_STRIP=y and the 'led-strip' DTS alias to be defined.
